            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-012-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 12:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not omitted,
                            see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיַּעַן
                                אִיֹּוב וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 12:1). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov
                                da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-012-fn2" type="footnote">Orignially misspelled as
                                <emph>talačuvlarnyn</emph>; corrected by the copyist.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-012-fn3" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>kip</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-012-fn4" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>da bavyn küčlülernin</emph>, introduced with the Hebrew phrase
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say’ the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וּמְזִיחַ אֲפִיקִים רִפָּה </foreign>
                            ‘and loosens the belt of the strong’. | C: <emph>quvatyn
                                küčlülärniŋ</emph>. | QB: <emph>quvatyn küčlülärniŋ</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>da bavyn küčlülernin</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>da bavyn ḱučĺuĺarnin</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
